        *   A "friends" table with columns like (student_id, friend_id)
        *   A "likes" table with columns like (student_id, liked_by_id)
        *   A single "relationships" table with columns like (student_id, related_student_id, relationship_type) where `relationship_type` could be "friend" or "likes".
