qwen_sql_builder responded: { "sql": "SELECT COUNT(c.contestant_number) AS contestants_without_votes FROM CONTESTANTS c LEFT JOIN VOTES v ON c.contestant_number = v.contestant_number WHERE v.contestant_number IS NULL;" , "explanation": [ { "step": "We start by selecting the count of contestant numbers from the CONTESTANTS table. This will give us the total number of contestants who did not receive any votes, as filtered by our conditions." }, { "step": "We use a LEFT JOIN between the CONTESTANTS and VOTES tables on the contestant_number column to ensure that all contestants are included in the result set, even those without corresponding entries in the VOTES table." }, { "step": "The WHERE clause filters out contestants who have received votes by checking for NULL values in the VOTES table's contestant_number column. This ensures we only count contestants with no votes." } ]}
Final SQL query: SELECT COUNT(c.contestant_number) AS contestants_without_votes FROM CONTESTANTS c LEFT JOIN VOTES v ON c.contestant_number = v.contestant_number WHERE v.contestant_number IS NULL;
